# Build-context exclusions for ``docker build .`` from repo root.
#
# Why this file exists: without it, Docker streams the entire working
# tree (~hundreds of MB of node_modules, .venv, .git, runs/, web/dist,
# JetBrains caches, etc.) into the daemon for EVERY rebuild, even when
# the Dockerfile doesn't reference those paths. With ``COPY src``
# becoming a routine line in our images, that cost gets paid on every
# layer cache miss. Keep this list tight and aligned with what the
# training / inference Dockerfiles actually need.

# --- VCS / IDE / editors ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.idea
.vscode
.cursor
.claude
.helix

# --- Python tooling state ---
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.coverage
**/.tox
**/.nox
.venv
venv
*.egg-info

# --- Frontend build artifacts ---
web/node_modules
web/dist
web/.vite
web/coverage
**/node_modules

# --- Runtime artifacts that the image must not bake in ---
# These are produced BY the pipeline at runtime and would leak host
# state into the image (and bloat it). The pipeline rsyncs fresh
# code into /workspace at deploy time anyway.
runs
mlruns
.mlflow

# --- Tests: not part of the runtime contract ---
# Rationale: the image ships the trainer, not its test suite. Tests
# also pull in dev-only deps (pytest, hypothesis) that aren't in
# requirements.runtime.txt — including them wouldn't even import.
packages/*/tests
tests

# --- Docs / plans / scratch ---
docs/plans
docs/audits
docs/architecture

# --- Local OS / env ---
.DS_Store
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Build outputs / logs ---
build
dist
*.egg
*.log
docker/training/build_and_push.log
docker/inference/build_and_push.log
